&lt;h2 data-start=&quot;162&quot; data-end=&quot;205&quot;&gt;Licensed Clinical Social Worker (LCSW)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;206&quot; data-end=&quot;228&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-start=&quot;206&quot; data-end=&quot;228&quot;&gt;In Person; Troy, NC | Full-Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;230&quot; data-end=&quot;396&quot;&gt;Peregrine Health partners with community health organizations to expand access to high-quality behavioral health care, delivered by supported, full-time clinicians.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;403&quot; data-end=&quot;429&quot;&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Direct Clinical Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct comprehensive biopsychosocial assessments to evaluate client needs, strengths, and risk factors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide individual, family, and group therapy using evidence-based modalities (CBT, DBT, trauma-informed care, motivational interviewing, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement individualized treatment plans in collaboration with clients and care team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and document client progress, adjusting treatment plans as clinically indicated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide crisis intervention, safety planning, and stabilization services as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Care Coordination &amp;amp; Advocacy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with physicians, nurses, case managers, and community health workers to ensure integrated, whole-person care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connect clients with community resources including housing assistance, food security programs, transportation, legal aid, and benefits enrollment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate warm handoffs and referrals to specialty mental health, substance use, or medical services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documentation &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete timely and accurate clinical documentation in the electronic health record (EHR) in accordance with organizational and regulatory standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain confidentiality and adhere to HIPAA and applicable state regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in quality improvement initiatives, case reviews, and outcome measurement efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Engagement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build trusting relationships with clients, families, and community partners across diverse cultural backgrounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in educational workshops&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a welcoming, culturally humble, and trauma-informed organizational environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 data-start=&quot;403&quot; data-end=&quot;429&quot;&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;433&quot; data-end=&quot;492&quot;&gt;Active Licensed Clinical Social Worker (LCSW) license&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;495&quot; data-end=&quot;606&quot;&gt;3+ years of post-licensure clinical experience (community mental health, integrated care, or similar settings preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
